CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F383A1782206308
OL,3,C'Plausible' forecast warns of 45C
OL,4,Chighs for Britain by middle of century
OL,6,FTemperatures across Britain could peak
OL,7,Fat 45C by the middle of the century as
OL,8,Fpart of a "plausible" heatwave
OL,9,Fforecast.
OL,11,FThe announcement by scientists and
OL,12,Fmeteorologists from several
OL,13,Finstitutions - including the
OL,14,FUniversity of Reading and the Met
OL,15,FOffice - comes amid what's predicted
OL,16,Fto be a record June heatwave.
OL,18,FIt's also coincided with the 50th
OL,19,Fanniversary of the 1976 heatwave,
OL,20,Fwhich saw existing temperature records
OL,21,Fset.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,384,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F383A1782206308
OL,3,C'Plausible' forecast warns of 45C
OL,4,Chighs for Britain by middle of century
OL,6,FOn that occasion a peak temperature of
OL,7,F35.9C was recorded on July 3, 1976.
OL,9,FThe Met Office forecasts that a 14-day
OL,10,Fsummer heatwave on June 23, 2056,
OL,11,Fcombined with future warming, would
OL,12,Fproduce peak temperatures of 45C in
OL,13,FEngland, 38C in Scotland, 41C in Wales
OL,14,Fand 30C in Belfast.
OL,16,FThat heatwave could also see
OL,17,Ftemperatures over 40C for nine days,
OL,18,Fthey warned - something the UK has
OL,19,Fseen only once, in the record heat of
OL,20,FJuly 2022.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,384,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F383A1782206308
OL,3,C'Plausible' forecast warns of 45C
OL,4,Chighs for Britain by middle of century
OL,6,FSubscribe for free to our weekly
OL,7,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,8,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,9,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,11,FHeatwaves and the hot dry summers,
OL,12,Fthey can occur in, carry rising risks
OL,13,Ffor people's health and ability to
OL,14,Fwork, learn and sit exams, for food
OL,15,Fsecurity, dangerous wildfires, huge
OL,16,Fwater shortages and impacts on the
OL,17,Fcountryside and nature.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,384,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F383A1782206308
OL,3,C'Plausible' forecast warns of 45C
OL,4,Chighs for Britain by middle of century
OL,6,FThe future forecast was presented in
OL,7,Fthe style of a TV weather forecast by
OL,8,Fpresenter and meteorologist Laura
OL,9,FTobin, at an event in London on Monday.
OL,11,FMs Tobin, who admitted at the event
OL,12,Fthat she had cried after giving the
OL,13,Fforecast of 40C in 2022 because of the
OL,14,Fimpact it would have on people, said:
OL,15,F"The idea that we will be living in
OL,16,Ftemperatures of 45C unless we
OL,17,Fsignificantly reduce fossil fuel
OL,18,Femissions is simply unimaginable.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,384,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F383A1782206308
OL,3,C'Plausible' forecast warns of 45C
OL,4,Chighs for Britain by middle of century
OL,6,F"As a mum, that doesn't feel like a
OL,7,Fweather statistic - It's terrifying,"
OL,8,Fshe said.
OL,10,FProfessor Ed Hawkins, from the
OL,11,FUniversity of Reading, said that "1976
OL,12,Fwas an extraordinary weather event,
OL,13,Fbut it took place in a much cooler
OL,14,Fworld", and a comparable heatwave
OL,15,Fwould be 3C hotter in today's much
OL,16,Fwarmer world.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,384,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F383A1782206308
OL,3,C'Plausible' forecast warns of 45C
OL,4,Chighs for Britain by middle of century
OL,6,FHe said: "The future 2056 forecast
OL,7,Ffrom the Met Office shows that people
OL,8,Fborn in 1976 could plausibly suffer
OL,9,F45C heat in their retirement years and
OL,10,Fchildren born today in 2026 will have
OL,11,Fto navigate such heatwaves in their
OL,12,F30s when they may be starting their
OL,13,Fown families."
OL,15,FReporting History sees journalists
OL,16,Fjoin News At Ten anchor Tom Bradby to
OL,17,Frevisit their remarkable on-the-day
OL,18,Freports of the defining events of the
OL,19,Fmodern age. Listen to the episodes
OL,20,Fbelow...
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/6
